{
    "publish_date": "2014-01-30T16:00:03.000Z", 
    "score": 0.0004992547226432744, 
    "video_length": "PT5M16S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "An enduring myth says we use", 
            "dur": "1.586", 
            "start": "6.494"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "only 10% of our brain.", 
            "dur": "1.832", 
            "start": "8.08"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The other 90% standing idly by for spare capacity.", 
            "dur": "3.589", 
            "start": "9.912"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Hucksters promised to unlock that hidden potential", 
            "dur": "2.923", 
            "start": "13.501"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "with methods &amp;quot;based on neuroscience,&amp;quot;", 
            "dur": "3.083", 
            "start": "16.424"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but all they really unlock is your wallet.", 
            "dur": "2.718", 
            "start": "19.507"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Two thirds of the public", 
            "dur": "1.249", 
            "start": "22.225"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and nearly half of science teachers", 
            "dur": "1.835", 
            "start": "23.474"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "mistakenly believe the 10% myth.", 
            "dur": "2.551", 
            "start": "25.309"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In the 1890s, William James,", 
            "dur": "2.199", 
            "start": "27.86"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the father of American psychology,", 
            "dur": "2", 
            "start": "30.059"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "said, &amp;quot;Most of us do not meet", 
            "dur": "1.883", 
            "start": "32.059"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "our mental potential.&amp;quot;", 
            "dur": "1.75", 
            "start": "33.942"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "James meant this as a challenge,", 
            "dur": "1.669", 
            "start": "35.692"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "not an indictment of scant brain usage.", 
            "dur": "2.465", 
            "start": "37.361"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But the misunderstanding stuck.", 
            "dur": "1.909", 
            "start": "39.826"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Also, scientists couldn&#39;t figure out", 
            "dur": "1.946", 
            "start": "41.735"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "for a long time", 
            "dur": "1.566", 
            "start": "43.681"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the purpose of our massive frontal lobes", 
            "dur": "2.33", 
            "start": "45.247"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "or broad areas of the parietal lobe.", 
            "dur": "2.586", 
            "start": "47.577"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Damage didn&#39;t cause motor or sensory deficits,", 
            "dur": "2.918", 
            "start": "50.163"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "so authorities concluded they didn&#39;t do anything.", 
            "dur": "3.458", 
            "start": "53.081"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "For decades, these parts", 
            "dur": "1.72", 
            "start": "56.539"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "were called silent areas,", 
            "dur": "1.946", 
            "start": "58.259"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "their function elusive.", 
            "dur": "1.001", 
            "start": "60.205"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We&#39;ve since learned that they underscore", 
            "dur": "1.807", 
            "start": "61.206"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "executive and integrative ability,", 
            "dur": "1.956", 
            "start": "63.013"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "without which, we would hardly be human.", 
            "dur": "2.254", 
            "start": "64.969"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "They are crucial to abstract reasoning,", 
            "dur": "2.04", 
            "start": "67.223"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "planning,", 
            "dur": "0.711", 
            "start": "69.263"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "weighing decisions", 
            "dur": "0.834", 
            "start": "69.974"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and flexibly adapting to circumstances.", 
            "dur": "2.877", 
            "start": "70.808"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The idea that 9/10 of your brain", 
            "dur": "1.839", 
            "start": "73.685"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "sits idly by in your skull", 
            "dur": "1.81", 
            "start": "75.524"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "looks silly when we calculate how the brain uses energy.", 
            "dur": "3.608", 
            "start": "77.334"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Rodent and canine brains consume", 
            "dur": "2.211", 
            "start": "80.942"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "5% of total body energy.", 
            "dur": "2.295", 
            "start": "83.153"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Monkey brains use 10%.", 
            "dur": "2.136", 
            "start": "85.448"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "An adult human brain,", 
            "dur": "1.536", 
            "start": "87.584"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which accounts for only 2% of the body&#39;s mass,", 
            "dur": "2.712", 
            "start": "89.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "consumes 20% of daily glucose burned.", 
            "dur": "3.961", 
            "start": "91.832"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In children, that figure is 50%,", 
            "dur": "2.457", 
            "start": "95.793"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and in infants, 60%.", 
            "dur": "2.631", 
            "start": "98.25"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This is far more than expected", 
            "dur": "1.537", 
            "start": "100.881"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "for their relative brain sizes,", 
            "dur": "1.8", 
            "start": "102.418"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which scale in proportion to body size.", 
            "dur": "2.418", 
            "start": "104.218"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Human ones weigh 1.5 kilograms,", 
            "dur": "2.281", 
            "start": "106.636"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "elephant brains 5 kg,", 
            "dur": "1.723", 
            "start": "108.917"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and whale brains 9 kg,", 
            "dur": "2.11", 
            "start": "110.64"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "yet on a per weight basis,", 
            "dur": "1.917", 
            "start": "112.75"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "humans pack in more neurons", 
            "dur": "1.852", 
            "start": "114.667"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "than any other species.", 
            "dur": "1.878", 
            "start": "116.519"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This dense packing is what makes us so smart.", 
            "dur": "3.129", 
            "start": "118.397"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "There is a trade-off between body size", 
            "dur": "2.042", 
            "start": "121.526"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and the number of neurons a primate,", 
            "dur": "2.046", 
            "start": "123.568"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "including us, can sustain.", 
            "dur": "1.812", 
            "start": "125.614"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "A 25 kg ape has to eat 8 hours a day", 
            "dur": "2.878", 
            "start": "127.426"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to uphold a brain with 53 billion neurons.", 
            "dur": "4.457", 
            "start": "130.304"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The invention of cooking,", 
            "dur": "1.256", 
            "start": "134.761"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "one and half million years ago,", 
            "dur": "1.358", 
            "start": "136.017"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "gave us a huge advantage.", 
            "dur": "1.968", 
            "start": "137.375"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Cooked food is rendered soft and predigested", 
            "dur": "3.017", 
            "start": "139.343"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "outside of the body.", 
            "dur": "1.507", 
            "start": "142.36"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Our guts more easily absorb its energy.", 
            "dur": "2.599", 
            "start": "143.867"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Cooking frees up time", 
            "dur": "1.462", 
            "start": "146.466"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and provides more energy", 
            "dur": "1.249", 
            "start": "147.928"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "than if we ate food stuffs raw", 
            "dur": "1.954", 
            "start": "149.177"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and so we can sustain brains", 
            "dur": "2.129", 
            "start": "151.131"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "with 86 billion densely packed neurons.", 
            "dur": "2.707", 
            "start": "153.26"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "40% more than the ape.", 
            "dur": "2.637", 
            "start": "155.967"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Here&#39;s how it works:", 
            "dur": "1.254", 
            "start": "158.604"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Half the calories a brain burns", 
            "dur": "1.875", 
            "start": "159.858"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "go towards simply keeping the structure intact", 
            "dur": "1.8", 
            "start": "161.733"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "by pumping sodium and potassium ions", 
            "dur": "3.299", 
            "start": "163.533"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "across membranes to maintain an electrical charge.", 
            "dur": "3.322", 
            "start": "166.832"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "To do this, the brain has to be an energy hog.", 
            "dur": "3.048", 
            "start": "170.154"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It consumes an astounding 3.4 x 10^21 ATP molecules per minute,", 
            "dur": "7.179", 
            "start": "173.202"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "ATP being the coal of the body&#39;s furnace.", 
            "dur": "3.119", 
            "start": "180.381"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The high cost of maintaining resting potentials", 
            "dur": "2.423", 
            "start": "183.5"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in all 86 billion neurons", 
            "dur": "2.264", 
            "start": "185.954"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "means that little energy is left", 
            "dur": "1.781", 
            "start": "188.218"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to propel signals down axons and across synapses,", 
            "dur": "3.584", 
            "start": "189.999"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the nerve discharges that actually get things done.", 
            "dur": "2.771", 
            "start": "193.583"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Even if only a tiny percentage of neurons", 
            "dur": "2.944", 
            "start": "196.369"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "fired in a given region at any one time,", 
            "dur": "2.864", 
            "start": "199.313"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the energy burden of generating spikes", 
            "dur": "2.599", 
            "start": "202.177"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "over the entire brain", 
            "dur": "1.369", 
            "start": "204.776"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "would be unsustainable.", 
            "dur": "1.834", 
            "start": "206.145"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Here&#39;s where energy efficiency comes in.", 
            "dur": "2.552", 
            "start": "207.979"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Letting just a small proportion of cells", 
            "dur": "2.364", 
            "start": "210.531"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "signal at any one time,", 
            "dur": "2", 
            "start": "212.895"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "known as sparse coding,", 
            "dur": "1.917", 
            "start": "214.895"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "uses the least energy,", 
            "dur": "1.56", 
            "start": "216.812"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but carries the most information.", 
            "dur": "2.294", 
            "start": "218.372"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Because the small number of signals", 
            "dur": "2.253", 
            "start": "220.666"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "have thousands of possible paths", 
            "dur": "1.811", 
            "start": "222.919"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "by which to distribute themselves.", 
            "dur": "2.25", 
            "start": "224.73"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "A drawback of sparse coding", 
            "dur": "1.48", 
            "start": "226.98"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "within a huge number of neurons", 
            "dur": "1.715", 
            "start": "228.46"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is its cost.", 
            "dur": "1.376", 
            "start": "230.175"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Worse, if a big proportion of cells never fire,", 
            "dur": "2.628", 
            "start": "231.551"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "then they are superfluous", 
            "dur": "1.42", 
            "start": "234.179"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and evolution should have jettisoned them long ago.", 
            "dur": "3.235", 
            "start": "235.599"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The solution is to find", 
            "dur": "1.569", 
            "start": "238.834"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the optimum proportion of cells", 
            "dur": "1.942", 
            "start": "240.403"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that the brain can have active at once.", 
            "dur": "2.051", 
            "start": "242.345"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "For maximum efficiency,", 
            "dur": "1.614", 
            "start": "244.396"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "between 1% and 16% of cells", 
            "dur": "2.642", 
            "start": "246.01"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "should be active at any given moment.", 
            "dur": "2.611", 
            "start": "248.652"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This is the energy limit", 
            "dur": "1.446", 
            "start": "251.263"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we have to live with", 
            "dur": "1.139", 
            "start": "252.709"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in order to be conscious at all.", 
            "dur": "1.504", 
            "start": "253.848"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The need to conserve resources", 
            "dur": "1.607", 
            "start": "255.352"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "is the reason most of the brain&#39;s operations", 
            "dur": "2.332", 
            "start": "256.959"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "must happen outside of conciousness.", 
            "dur": "2.431", 
            "start": "259.291"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It&#39;s why multitasking is a fool&#39;s errand.", 
            "dur": "2.471", 
            "start": "261.722"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "We simply lack the energy to do two things at once", 
            "dur": "2.778", 
            "start": "264.193"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "let alone three or five.", 
            "dur": "1.812", 
            "start": "266.971"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "When we try, we do each task less well", 
            "dur": "2.132", 
            "start": "268.783"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "than if we had given it our full attention.", 
            "dur": "2.328", 
            "start": "270.915"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The numbers are against us.", 
            "dur": "1.729", 
            "start": "273.243"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Your brain is already smart and powerful.", 
            "dur": "2.439", 
            "start": "274.972"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So powerful, that it needs a lot of power", 
            "dur": "2.31", 
            "start": "277.411"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to stay powerful.", 
            "dur": "1.333", 
            "start": "279.721"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And so smart", 
            "dur": "1.2", 
            "start": "281.054"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that it has built in an energy efficiency plan.", 
            "dur": "3.168", 
            "start": "282.254"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So don&#39;t let a fradulent myth", 
            "dur": "1.587", 
            "start": "285.422"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "make you guilty about your", 
            "dur": "1.499", 
            "start": "287.009"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "supposedly lazy brain.", 
            "dur": "1.315", 
            "start": "288.508"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Guilt would be a waste of energy.", 
            "dur": "1.94", 
            "start": "289.823"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "After all this,", 
            "dur": "0.874", 
            "start": "291.763"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "don&#39;t you realize it&#39;s dumb to waste", 
            "dur": "1.584", 
            "start": "292.637"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "mental energy?", 
            "dur": "1.084", 
            "start": "294.221"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "You have billions of", 
            "dur": "1.166", 
            "start": "295.305"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "power-hungry neurons to maintain.", 
            "dur": "1.633", 
            "start": "296.471"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So hop to it!", 
            "dur": "1.706", 
            "start": "298.104"
        }
    ], 
